gravit
------------------------------------------
Gravit is a free, visually stunning gravity simulator, where you can spend
endless time experimenting with various configurations of simulated universes.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.2-1
  libGL1-19.1.6-1
  libGLU1-9.0.2-1
  libSDL1.2_0-1.2.15-3
  libSDL_image1.2_0-1.2.12-6
  libSDL_ttf2.0_0-2.0.11-1
  libgomp1-12.4.0-3
  libpng16-1.6.47-2
  lua5.1-5.1.5-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  autoconf-archive-2024.10.16-1
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.44-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  gcc-g++-12.4.0-3
  libGL-devel-19.1.6-1
  libGLU-devel-9.0.2-1
  libSDL-devel-1.2.15-3
  libSDL_image-devel-1.2.12-6
  libSDL_ttf-devel-2.0.11-1
  libpng-devel-1.6.47-2
  lua5.1-devel-5.1.5-3
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/gak/gravit

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/gak/gravit/archive/refs/tags/0.5.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack gravit-0.5.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./gravit-0.5.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/gravit-0.5.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/gravit-0.5.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

